Acts 1-1 <pb/>In the first book, O <f>ⓐ</f>Theophilus, I have dealt with all that Jesus began <f>ⓑ</f>to do and teach,
Acts 1-2 until the day when <f>ⓒ</f>he was taken up, after he <f>ⓓ</f>had given commands <f>ⓔ</f>through the Holy Spirit to the apostles whom he had chosen.
Acts 1-3 <f>ⓕ</f> He presented himself alive to them after his suffering by many proofs, appearing to them during forty days and speaking about the kingdom of God.
Acts 1-4 <pb/>And while staying <f>[1]</f> with them <f>ⓖ</f>he ordered them not to depart from Jerusalem, but to wait for the promise of the Father, which, he said, <J>“you heard from me;</J>
