Acts 1-21 <pb/>So one of the men who have accompanied us during <f>ⓤ</f>all the time that the Lord Jesus <f>ⓥ</f>went in and out among us,
Acts 1-22 <f>ⓦ</f> beginning from the baptism of John until the day when <f>ⓧ</f>he was taken up from us — one of these men must become with us <f>ⓨ</f>a witness to his resurrection.”
Acts 1-23 And they put forward two, Joseph called <f>ⓩ</f>Barsabbas, who was also called <f>ⓐ</f>Justus, and <f>ⓑ</f>Matthias.
